{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πέλᾰς</b>, <br /> <i>adverb</i> <b>near, hard by</b>, with <i>genitive</i>, which commonly stands before π., Τηλεμάχου π. ἵστατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.257 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; Νείλου π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 308, compare “Ag.” 1038, 1671 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; καὶ τάδ᾽ ἀγχόνης π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 246, compare “HF” 1109 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also before its case, π. τῆς Κασταλίης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.39, compare 138; αὕτη π. σοῦ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1474 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; separated from its case, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ant.” 580. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>dative</i>, π. ἐμβόλῳ, σκάπτῳ π., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.18, “N.” 11.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σοὶ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 208, compare “fragment” 102. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, χριμφθεὶς πέλας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.516 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. στείχειν, παρεῖναι, παραστατεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 877, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 83, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 669. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> οἱ π. (i.e. ὄντες) <b>one's neighbours</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 293, 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista 58, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.97, 5th c.BC: Critias Philosophus, Tragicus, Elegiacus 15.6 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.69, 4.78, 92, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1169a14, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>one's fellow creatures</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 2, “Hipp.” 441 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ τῶν πέλας κακά, opposed to τὰ οἰκήϊα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.152: _sing._, ὁ π\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <b>one's neighbour</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.142, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.32; πᾶς τις αὑτὸν τοῦ π. μᾶλλον φιλεῖ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 86 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; compare πλησίον. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>superlative</i> πελαστάτω <b>nearest</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Loc. Hom.” 12, 45, “Mul.” 1.66 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: a <i>superlative</i> <i>adjective</i> πελάστατος, η, ον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 14.352 ii65 (from Halaesa). \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8681","accentedUnicode":"πέλας","shortDef":"a one near","mediumDef":"a one near","stepGloss":"a one near","stepTransliteration":"pelas","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}